{
    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": "intro_naming_rules",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Naming Rules & Assignments",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Now that you know how to create and use variables, let's learn the rules for naming them properly. Good variable names make your code easier to read and understand."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "variable_naming_rules",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Variable Naming Rules",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Python has specific rules for variable names. Following these rules helps you avoid errors."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "start_with_letter",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Variable names must **start with a letter** or underscore (_)."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"Alice\"\n\n_age = 25",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "no_spaces",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Variable names **cannot contain spaces** or special characters."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "# Wrong - has space\nmy name = \"Bob\"",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "case_sensitive",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Python is **case-sensitive**. `name`, `Name`, and `NAME` are different variables."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"Alice\"\nName = \"Bob\"\nNAME = \"Charlie\"\n\nprint(name)\nprint(Name)\nprint(NAME)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Alice\nBob\nCharlie"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "valid_variable_names",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Here are some examples of **valid** variable names."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "name = \"Alice\"\n_age = 25\nstudent1 = \"Bob\"",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "invalid_variable_names",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Here are some examples of **invalid** variable names."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "#can't start with a numbers\n2name = \"Alice\"\n\n#no spaces allowed\nmy name = \"Bob\"\n\n#can't use special characters\nuser@email = \"test\"",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
